Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora from neck join to moderate turn. Clay fine red-brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Pencil '734'. Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 101a 38, 110 8 or 206 29. Name Boethos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX CR1 0161.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0509)
